00:41:30,905 --> 00:41:32,740
He's hitting shots.

690
00:41:32,823 --> 00:41:37,036
Phil said, you know, forcefully,
"Paxson is open, get him the ball."

691
00:41:37,119 --> 00:41:38,954
And I started looking for Paxson.

692
00:41:39,038 --> 00:41:43,501
Everybody in the world's expecting Jordan
to force something through a double team.

693
00:41:44,960 --> 00:41:46,712
He doesn't do it. He draws and dishes.

694
00:41:47,588 --> 00:41:49,298
<i>Paxson open again...</i>

695
00:41:50,090 --> 00:41:53,469
He trusts his teammate to make the shot.

696
00:41:53,552 --> 00:41:57,389
Once Pax hits that first shot,
"Oh, okay. Fine.

697
00:41:57,473 --> 00:42:00,142
Let me do this again.
Penetrate, find Pax."

698
00:42:00,226 --> 00:42:02,645
And he kept hitting 'em, kept hitting 'em.

699
00:42:02,728 --> 00:42:05,231
<i>Again! Eighteen for Paxson!</i>

700
00:42:05,314 --> 00:42:08,609
That was exactly what Phil was trying
to get Michael to understand

701
00:42:08,692 --> 00:42:10,694
and believe in over the couple years,
is that,

702
00:42:10,778 --> 00:42:12,571
"These other guys can help you out."

703
00:42:12,655 --> 00:42:16,033
<i>It is a two-point lead
for Chicago.</i>

704
00:42:16,116 --> 00:42:17,243
<i>Paxson!</i>

705
00:42:17,326 --> 00:42:20,162
<i>Yes! John Paxson again!</i>

706
00:42:20,788 --> 00:42:26,585
<i>The Chicago Bulls have won
their first-ever NBA championship!</i>

707
00:42:54,363 --> 00:42:55,614
You did it the right way.

708
00:42:55,698 --> 00:42:56,991
You did it the right way.

709
00:43:02,496 --> 00:43:03,330
I love you.

710
00:43:03,414 --> 00:43:04,623
- Scottie...
- Yes!

711
00:43:11,547 --> 00:43:14,883
<i>When you get to that finish line
and you know that you won...</i>

712
00:43:14,967 --> 00:43:17,595
<i>all those emotions
that you wrapped up into,</i>

713
00:43:17,678 --> 00:43:18,929
<i>you can just let go.</i>

714
00:43:19,013 --> 00:43:20,347
I'm so happy.

715
00:43:23,434 --> 00:43:24,643
Everybody knows...

716
00:43:24,727 --> 00:43:28,981
Has the picture in their mind of
when we beat Cleveland on that last shot

717
00:43:29,064 --> 00:43:31,692
and he's punching the air,
he's all excited.

718
00:43:31,775 --> 00:43:35,571
That's who we knew,
the competitive Michael Jordan.

719
00:43:37,948 --> 00:43:39,867
The win-at-all-costs Michael Jordan.

720
00:43:41,910 --> 00:43:44,121
Sometimes we'd question
whether he was human,

721
00:43:44,622 --> 00:43:46,081
whether he had feelings.

722
00:43:47,541 --> 00:43:50,753
A guy that was totally focused
on one thing and one thing only.

723
00:43:51,712 --> 00:43:53,756
The only emotion
we had ever seen out of him

724
00:43:53,839 --> 00:43:55,299
was anger or frustration.

725
00:43:55,966 --> 00:43:59,303
We were literally stunned
to see those emotions.

726
00:44:01,180 --> 00:44:02,389
Seven-year struggle.

727
00:44:02,973 --> 00:44:04,058
Seven-year struggle.

728
00:44:06,852 --> 00:44:09,563
And when they beat us, well,

729
00:44:09,647 --> 00:44:14,068
we met in between both locker rooms,
and he put his arms...

730
00:44:14,652 --> 00:44:15,653
<i>and started crying.</i>

731
00:44:15,736 --> 00:44:19,239
<i>He was so happy that he had won,
that he busted through.</i>

732
00:44:19,323 --> 00:44:23,202
<i>That was a special moment
for him and myself.</i>

733
00:44:23,952 --> 00:44:25,496
It's a beautiful feeling.

734
00:44:25,579 --> 00:44:27,539
If you're gonna lose, you lose to them.

735
00:44:27,623 --> 00:44:29,375
I'm going to lose to Michael.

736
00:44:29,458 --> 00:44:31,919
And that... That's how...
how it should be.

737
00:44:33,420 --> 00:44:36,173
At last, I fit somewhere in

738
00:44:36,256 --> 00:44:39,009
the category of Larry Bird
and Magic Johnson.

739
00:45:10,249 --> 00:45:11,709
Shit! C'mon, drop my money down.

